I got a question on verilator. I am trying to write a testbench for an AES encryption module. This module contains 2 inputs of 128 bits and 1 output of same size.

types in verilator are:

```
 VL_IN8(clk,0,0);
 //char	__VpadToAlign1[7];
 VL_INW(state,127,0,4);
 VL_INW(key,127,0,4);
 VL_OUTW(out,127,0,4);

```

I was wondering what type of variable suite them in c++ testbench. would it be arrays of char? 

would you have by any chance any example of a testbench that drives a module with such large ports? I could help me to understand how to write such testbenches better.
